-- Croatia's economy to shrink 0.6 pct in 2014 - cenbank governor
-- By Igor Ilic
-- Thu Oct 16, 2014 03:44AM EDT
-- None



ROVINJ, Croatia, Oct 16 (Reuters) - Croatia's economy will shrink 0.6 percent this year, the central bank governor said on Thursday, cutting the bank's July forecast of a 0.2 percent decline for the newest European Union member, which has had no growth since 2008.

